{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":251233,"duration_api_ms":251086,"num_turns":35,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a2bafe77-a0ec-4c79-91ab-8b0bb7083566","total_cost_usd":1.3049334500000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":34,"cache_creation_input_tokens":50173,"cache_read_input_tokens":1503865,"output_tokens":8299,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":50173,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":34,"outputTokens":8299,"cacheReadInputTokens":1503865,"cacheCreationInputTokens":50173,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.2731587500000003,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":32,"outputTokens":2140,"cacheReadInputTokens":104727,"cacheCreationInputTokens":8456,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.031774699999999996,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All five amendments identify genuine defects. Two are clear bugs (b2220aa1: stale retry bookkeeping causes incorrect resume attempt number; 39fd79cd: best-effort snapshot write defeats crash-during-backoff recovery). Two are robustness/quality issues (a210d3ba: poor jitter entropy source; fd63d152: unbounded dead entry accumulation). One addresses test fragility (3303d1eb: start_paused coupling to Tokio internals). All accepted after code verification.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-17-fd63d152","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at engine.rs:5843-5852: the CycleAdvanced handler increments current_cycle but never prunes retryable_failed_attempts entries keyed to prior cycles. While these entries are functionally dead (lookups use the new cycle number), they accumulate indefinitely across remediation cycles. The proposed retain(|&(_, c), _| c >= current_cycle) is safe — it can't remove entries for the current or future cycles — and mirrors CompletionRoundAdvanced's .clear() at line 5865. Zero-risk cleanup of unnecessary memory growth."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-a210d3ba","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at retry_policy.rs:134-143: apply_jitter uses SystemTime::now().subsec_nanos() % 1000, yielding only 1000 distinct values and producing identical results when called within the same nanosecond-granularity window. For consecutive retry attempts of the same stage (exactly the thundering-herd scenario jitter is meant to prevent), calls are separated only by the failure detection time, which can be sub-millisecond in the stub/test path. Mixing in the attempt number (e.g., nanos.wrapping_add(attempt * 397) % 1000) guarantees distinct jitter across consecutive retries with zero new dependencies and is the most pragmatic fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-3303d1eb","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at process_backend_test.rs:2169-2207: the test uses start_paused=true with a real OS process (sleep 99999). It works because: the adapter drops stdin causing 'cat > /dev/null' to exit and sleep to start, stdout/stderr reach EOF immediately (inherited pipes close), leaving only the process wait() as pending OS I/O alongside the 2-second timer. Tokio's auto-advance then fires the timer. This chain depends on Tokio's auto-advance triggering when only OS I/O and timers are pending — an implementation detail not guaranteed across versions. At minimum, a comment explaining this mechanism is warranted. Cheap fix, prevents future confusion during Tokio upgrades."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-b2220aa1","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed real bug via code tracing. At engine.rs:5836-5840, StageFailed only inserts into retryable_failed_attempts when will_retry=true. When retries exhaust (attempt 5, will_retry=false for TransportFailure with default max_attempts=5), the entry is never removed. retryable_failed_attempts still holds (stage_id, cycle) -> 4. At lines 5899-5902, resume_attempt = 4 + 1 = 5, but SC-RESUME-005 (scenarios.rs:4634-4642) asserts attempt=1. The fix is straightforward: add an else branch on will_retry=false that calls retryable_failed_attempts.remove(&(stage_id, cycle)). This is the most impactful amendment — it's a confirmed functional bug with a failing conformance test."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-39fd79cd","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at engine.rs:4563-4600 and 4643-4657. The stage_failed event (with will_retry=true) is durably appended to the journal BEFORE the snapshot write. If write_run_snapshot fails (caught and logged as warn at line 4651-4656) and the process then crashes during backoff, the journal records 'failed, retrying' while run.json remains in Running status — exactly the non-resumable state this snapshot was introduced to prevent. The code's own comment (lines 4646-4650) acknowledges the failure mode but dismisses it as 'same state as before this snapshot was introduced,' which contradicts the feature's raison d'être. The write should propagate the error or retry, not silently degrade to the pre-feature behavior."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a46439d4-6430-450e-95ed-cad7719b7002"}
